<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 4:17PM MDT  by NWS Boulder</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Weld
County through 500 PM MDT...
At 417 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
New Raymer, or 26 miles north of Fort Morgan, moving northeast at 15
mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Stoneham and New Raymer.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
